title: Potential delay on some upgrades to gov't insurance site
text:
> Business Potential delay on some upgrades to gov't insurance site FILE - In this Oct. 6, 2015 file photo, the HealthCare.gov website, where people can buy health insurance, is displayed on a laptop screen in Washington. With sign-up season starting in just two weeks, the Obama administration is indicating on Oct. 19, that some long-awaited upgrades to the government's health insurance website could take more time.
